args: You said that kidnapper-type was seen\nover here, Mordecai?
That's what I heard, but I fear the snow\nhas covered up any possible clues.
And now it's dark. Dammit, if we don't find\nthose kids soon, there's no telling what\nmight happen to them...
Damn that girl! I got squat today cause'a\nher, so I gotta find me some scratch!
Well, he certainly didn't get my message\nlast time, because now he's trying to\nbreak into that store!
What are you going to do, Ilia?
I know we're supposed to be finding clues\nabout the kidnapper, but this guy is REALLY\ntorquing my chain...
We can't just ignore something bad\nhappening right in front of us! C'mon!
Crikey, but feedin' all'a them snatched rug\nrats costs a pretty penny, and no mistake.
HOLD IT RIGHT THERE, BUSTER!\nJUST WHAT DID YOU MEAN BY THAT?!
Aw, crap! It's that lady what chased me\nall over hell'n breakfast earlier!\nLemme go, ya daft chickadee!
You might as well stop struggling.\nYou're not going anywhere.
Now then, what was that little aside you\njust had about ＂feeding rug rats?＂

You sure? 'Cause you can either talk to
me, or I can drag you over to the local
guard and tell them all about your little
crime spree.

I'm pretty sure THEIR investigations are
much more harsh than mine. Who knows
when you'll ever see the outside again
after they lock you up?
I was just tryin' to get money what so we\ncould feed all them kids we snatched up!
So you're stealing money in order to\nfeed stolen kids?
Oy, them kids are precious bargaining\nchips! Can't have 'em keelin' over on us,\nnow can we?

We're holdin' all of 'em for ransom, yeah?
Their parents are all rich as anything,
so once they find their wee darlings are
gone, they'll pay through the nose!
Kya ha ha! Easiest plan ever, actually.\nThem kids'll follow Saint Starfall anywhere\ndurin' Dragonyule, so they will!
Been doin' it for years now, we have,\nand it's always a right trig business.
Committing crimes on top of crimes is too\nrisky to be a smart business, if you ask me.
Ain't ya never heard'a high risk'n high\nreward, girlie? We pull this off one day a\nyear and it feeds us the other 364!
Until you are captured in the act\nas you now have been.
Aw, dry bones to ya both! I done went and\nspilled me guts, so ya gotta let me go.\nThat was the deal!
That was most specifically NOT the deal.\nNow show me where your hideout is.
...There it is, ya stubborn arse.\nThat's where all'a them kids be.
Thanks for the help. Now get some sleep.
How's it sound in there, Mordecai?
I can hear the children's voices,\nas well as that of an adult man.
In that case, all that's left is to launch our\nsurprise atta—
Damn Ben always takes ages to get\nbaaaa... Huh? Who the hell are you?!
Right! Plan B: Charge in fists swinging!
Mordecai, you take care of the kids\nwhile I sort these jokers out!
I don't think you've got the skills to talk\nand fight at the same time!
Enough of this! Grab the children!\nUse them as shields!
I won't let you touch them.
How long can you withstand our attacks\nand protect those children, eh?
Enough of this! Hand the children over,\nand you may walk out with your lives!
Tch! What the hell are those worthless\nsubordinates of mine doing?!
Sorry, buddy, but they're in dreamland.\nIt's just you against me now.
You can't dodge me in midair, fool!
She used the blast to right herself?\nWhat IS that weapon?!
Mana output at maximum.\nGoing in full throttle!
Yeah, I'm good. What about the kids?
No surprise there... Don't worry, kiddos!\nWe're gonna get you home.
I WON'T LET IT END HERE!
(Shoot! I was too slow! He's gonna—!)
